@node "MAST" "TrackDisplayClock"

@{MS "TrackDisplayClock"}

Well, there isnÇt much to say! Its possible to configurate TrackDisplayClock via CLI, GUI and
ToolTypes.@{par}

@{b}Generaly I suggest not to insert unprotected disks while the clock is running. I never had any
problems, but there may be a little chance of loosing data.@{ub}
@{code}

   @{"CXPopKey" link "MASTCXPK"}
   @{"CXPriority" link "MASTCXPr"}
   @{"CXPopUp" link "MASTCXPU"}

   @{"DeActivate HotKey" link "MASTDeAc"}

   @{"Save" link "MASTSAVE"}
   @{"Use" link "MASTOKOK"}
   @{"Cancel" link "MASTCANC"}

@endnode
@node "MASTCXPK" "The Preferences: CXPopKey"

@{MS "CXPopKey"}

This gadget allows to specify the key combination to open the GUI.

@endnode
@node "MASTCXPr" "The Preferences: CXPriority"

@{MS "CXPriority"}

This defines the commodity priority. You shouldnÇt change this without a good reason!

@endnode
@node "MASTCXPU" "The Preferences: CXPopUp"

@{MS "CXPopUp"}

Use this switch to force the GUI to open on each startup! Otherwise disable it.

@endnode
@node "MASTDeAc" "The Preferences: DeActivate Hotkey"

@{MS "DeActivate Hotkey"}

Here you can specify a hotkey to quick activate/deactivate disk access. Pressing the hotkey will
force TrackDisplayClock to release the trackdisk.device. Press this combination again to reactivate
the clock and deactivate disk access again.@{par}

@{b}You must not press this hotkey during disk access! This may cause real disk errors even when
only reading!@{ub}

@endnode
@node "MASTSave" "The Preferences: Save"

@{MS "Save"}

The settings will be saved into TrackDisplayClocks icon and used as well. The settings window will
close imediatly.

@endnode
@node "MASTOkOk" "The Preferences: Use"

@{MS "Use"}

The window will be closed and the settings used, but the settings wonÇt be saved!

@endnode
@node "MASTCanc" "The Preferences: Cancel"

@{MS "Cancel"}

This button closes the window and all changed settings are lost!

@endnode

